rlSsh.name: rlSsh
rlSsh.description: The MIB module describes the private MIB for SSH supported by Dell's software and products.

RlSshPublicKeyAlgorithm.name: RlSshPublicKeyAlgorithm
RlSshPublicKeyAlgorithm.description: This textual convention describes the various possible public key algorithms. The key algorithm is used to select the PK to be generated and is also used when viewing the public keys.

RlSshPublicKeyDigestFormat.name: RlSshPublicKeyDigestFormat
RlSshPublicKeyDigestFormat.description: This textual convention describes the format used to display the public key fingerprint. The hex format is the format used by PGP and OpenSSH. The bubble-babble format is used by SSH.com software.

rlSshMibVersion.name: rlSshMibVersion
rlSshMibVersion.description: The MIB version. The current version is 2

rlSshServerHostPublicKeyTable.name: rlSshServerHostPublicKeyTable
rlSshServerHostPublicKeyTable.description: This table contains the router's public key. Each row in this table contains a fragment of the key, in printable binhex format. There may be up to 160 characters in every fragment, and they are all combined to form one key. The key is generated by writing to rlSshServerRegenerateHostKey. To cause clients to connect to this router without printing warning messages (and also prevent active man-in-the-middle), the router's public key must printed out and inserted into the client's authorized_keys file

rlSshServerHostPublicKeyTableEntry.name: rlSshServerHostPublicKeyTableEntry
rlSshServerHostPublicKeyTableEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlSshServerHostPublicKeyAlgorithm.name: rlSshServerHostPublicKeyAlgorithm
rlSshServerHostPublicKeyAlgorithm.description: Identifies the type of public key to be displayed.

rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFragmentId.name: rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFragmentId
rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFragmentId.description: Identifies the index of this fragment in the final key. All segments must be combined to form one big key.

rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFragmentText.name: rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFragmentText
rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFragmentText.description: A part of the readable text entry for the server's public authorzation key.

rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFingerprintTable.name: rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFingerprintTable
rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFingerprintTable.description: This table contains the fingerprint for the router's public key.

rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFingerprintTable.description: The row definition for this table.

rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFingerprintAlgor.description: Identifies the type of public key to be displayed.

rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFingerprintDiges.name: rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFingerprintDigestFormat
rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFingerprintDiges.description: Format of the digest to be displayed (OpenSSH or SSH.com).

rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFingerprint.name: rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFingerprint
rlSshServerHostPublicKeyFingerprint.description: SECSH format fingerprint of the server's public key. To prevent man in the middle attacks, users should make sure the ssh Server's fingerprint, as printed in the connection process, is similar to the one printed here.

rlSshServerAuthorizedUsersPublicKeyTable.name: rlSshServerAuthorizedUsersPublicKeyTable
rlSshServerAuthorizedUsersPublicKeyTable.description: This table contains public keys for all users who are authorized to access the router. For a user to be able to log in using SSH, the user name must appear in this table, and the user's public key must match the one found here.

rlSshServerAuthorizedUsersPublicKeyTable.description: The row definition for this table.

rlSshServerAuthorizedUserName.name: rlSshServerAuthorizedUserName
rlSshServerAuthorizedUserName.description: Name of the user who owns this public key. Both the user name and the key bytes must match before a user is authenticated using this key.

rlSshServerAuthorizedUserPublicKeyFragme.name: rlSshServerAuthorizedUserPublicKeyFragmentId
rlSshServerAuthorizedUserPublicKeyFragme.description: Identifies the index of this fragment in the final key. All segments must be combined to form one big key.

rlSshServerAuthorizedUserPublicKeyFragme.name: rlSshServerAuthorizedUserPublicKeyFragmentText
rlSshServerAuthorizedUserPublicKeyFragme.description: A part of the readable text entry for the user's public authorzation key.

rlSshServerAuthorizedUserPublicKeyFragme.name: rlSshServerAuthorizedUserPublicKeyFragmentStatus
rlSshServerAuthorizedUserPublicKeyFragme.description: Create or delete a fragment of the user's public key. A user is deleted if it has no remaining fragments.

rlSshServerAuthorizedUsersPublicKeyFinge.description: This table contains the fingerprints of the public keys for all users who are authorized to access the router. To prevent man in the middle attacks, users should make sure the user's fingerprint, as printed in the connection process, is similar to the one printed here.

rlSshServerImportExportSelfKeyTable.name: rlSshServerImportExportSelfKeyTable
rlSshServerImportExportSelfKeyTable.description: This table can be used for 2 purposes: 1) Importing public/private key pair to serve as the device key when acting as SSH server. This is done by setting entries to this table, according to the specified format. When the last entry (footer) is set, the whole key pair is checked and if valid, stored in CDB. 2) Exporting the device SSH server public/private key. This can be done by performing GetNext operations on this table.

The following formats are supported for import/export: 1) uuencoded_format - in this format both private and public key are in uu-encoded format, and are seperated from one another by header and footer. rlSshServerPort.name: rlSshServerPort
rlSshServerPort.description: Specifies the TCP port used by the SSH 2 Server to listen for incoming connections.

rlSshServerEnable.name: rlSshServerEnable
rlSshServerEnable.description: Enables listening for incoming SSH2 connections on the port defined in rlSshServerPort.

rlSshServerEnablePublicKeyAuthentication.name: rlSshServerEnablePublicKeyAuthentication
rlSshServerEnablePublicKeyAuthentication.description: If PK authentication is enabled, incoming SSH connections are authenticated using public key authentication (using rlSshServerAuthorizedUsersPublicKeyTable), before authenticating using the router's standard AAA.

rlSshServerRegenerateHostKey.name: rlSshServerRegenerateHostKey
rlSshServerRegenerateHostKey.description: Setting to a value other than none results in the Server (Host) Key being regenerated. The key size is host-specific.

rlSshServerDefaultKeyFlag.name: rlSshServerDefaultKeyFlag
rlSshServerDefaultKeyFlag.description: This scalar indicates which of the SSH server keys are default keys (automatically generated).

rlSshServerDeleteSelfKey.name: rlSshServerDeleteSelfKey
rlSshServerDeleteSelfKey.description: Setting to a value other than 'none' results in deleting the server self key of the chosen type. As a result a default key may be created (according to the MTSC..)

rlSshServerEnablePublicKeyAuthAutoLogin.name: rlSshServerEnablePublicKeyAuthAutoLogin
rlSshServerEnablePublicKeyAuthAutoLogin.description: If PK authentication is succesfull and AAA local DB method is enabled for SSH line, the username is checked with AAA local DB. If present, the user is authenticated automatically without prompting for username or password.

rlSshServerEnablePasswordAuthentication.name: rlSshServerEnablePasswordAuthentication
rlSshServerEnablePasswordAuthentication.description: If password authentication is enabled, incoming SSH connections are authenticated with username/password authentication using the router's standard AAA.

rlSshClientUserName.name: rlSshClientUserName
rlSshClientUserName.description: Specifies the default user name the ssh client will use when authenticating to a remote server. In SCP sessions this global user name will be used unless a specific user name has been specified for the operation. The value of this MIB must not contain charachters ':' or '@' (those are used to indicate parameters seperation in SCP copy).

rlSshClientRegenerateSelfKey.name: rlSshClientRegenerateSelfKey
rlSshClientRegenerateSelfKey.description: Setting to a value other than none results in the client self key being regenerated. The key size is host-specific.

rlSshClientSelfPublicKeyTable.name: rlSshClientSelfPublicKeyTable
rlSshClientSelfPublicKeyTable.description: This table contains the router's client self public key. Each row in this table contains a fragment of the key, in printable binhex format. There may be up to 160 characters in every fragment, and they are all combined to form one key. The key is generated by writing to rlSshClientRegenerateSelfKey. To cause clients to connect to this router without printing warning messages (and also prevent active man-in-the-middle), the router's public key must printed out and inserted into the client's authorized_keys file

rlSshClientSelfPublicKeyAlgorithm.description: Identifies the type of public key to be displayed.

rlSshClientSelfPublicKeyFragmentText.name: rlSshClientSelfPublicKeyFragmentText
rlSshClientSelfPublicKeyFragmentText.description: A part of the readable text entry for the router's client public authorization key.

rlSshClientSelfPublicKeyFingerprintTable.description: This table contains the fingerprint for the client's self key.

rlSshClientSelfPublicKeyFingerprintTable.description: The row definition for this table.

rlSshClientSelfPublicKeyFingerprintDiges.description: Format of the digest to be displayed (OpenSSH or SSH.com).

rlSshClientSelfPublicKeyFingerprint.description: SECSH format fingerprint of the client's self key. To prevent man in the middle attacks, users should make sure the ssh Server's fingerprint, as printed in the connection process, is similar to the one printed here.

rlSshClientAuthenticationMethod.name: rlSshClientAuthenticationMethod
rlSshClientAuthenticationMethod.description: Specifies the global authentication method for SSH client. SSH client will apply this authentication method upon connecting to a remote server, if no specific authentication method has been defined for this operation.

rlSshClientPassword.name: rlSshClientPassword
rlSshClientPassword.description: Specifies the global password for SSH client, to be used for 'password' authentication. SSH client will use this password during authentication phase (when connecting remote server), in case no specific password has been specified for this operation. The value of this MIB must not contain charachters ':' or '@' (those are used to indicate parameters seperation in SCP copy). Upon setting the password, its length must be in range 1-70.

rlSshClientPasswordChangeTable.name: rlSshClientPasswordChangeTable
rlSshClientPasswordChangeTable.description: This table allows the user to change the password in a remote SSH server. It should be used when working with 'password' authentication with remote server in SCP sessions. Set operation on this table will initiate SCP session with the SSH server whose inet address is specified in the key rlSshClientPasswordChangeInetAddress. During this session the password for username rlSshClientPasswordChangeUsername will be changed in the server from rlSshClientPasswordChangeOldPassword to rlSshClientPasswordChangeNewPassword. The Set operation might fail, in case an SCP session is already being held. In case 'noError' is returned, the user can poll the fields rlSshClientPasswordChangeStatus and rlSshClientPasswordChangeFailureReason in order to get information on operation status and possible failure reason. Note: up to 3 status records can be saved.

rlSshClientPasswordChangeEntry.name: rlSshClientPasswordChangeEntry
rlSshClientPasswordChangeEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlSshClientPasswordChangeInetAddrType.name: rlSshClientPasswordChangeInetAddrType
rlSshClientPasswordChangeInetAddrType.description: Specifies the inet address type of remote SCP server

rlSshClientPasswordChangeInetAddr.name: rlSshClientPasswordChangeInetAddr
rlSshClientPasswordChangeInetAddr.description: Specifies the inet address of remote SCP server

rlSshClientPasswordChangeUsername.name: rlSshClientPasswordChangeUsername
rlSshClientPasswordChangeUsername.description: Specifies the username for which the password change is required.

rlSshClientPasswordChangeOldPassword.name: rlSshClientPasswordChangeOldPassword
rlSshClientPasswordChangeOldPassword.description: Specifies the old password that was in use for rlSshClientPasswordChangeUsername until now. Upon setting a value in this entry, length of this field value must be 6-70. Password of length 0 will always be returned on GET operations.

rlSshClientPasswordChangeNewPassword.name: rlSshClientPasswordChangeNewPassword
rlSshClientPasswordChangeNewPassword.description: Specifies the new password that should be in use for rlSshClientPasswordChangeUsername from now on. Upon setting a value in this entry, length of this field value must be 6-70. Password of length 0 will always be returned on GET operations.

rlSshClientPasswordChangeStatus.name: rlSshClientPasswordChangeStatus
rlSshClientPasswordChangeStatus.description: Specifies the status of last password change operation on remote server identified by rlSshClientPasswordChangeInetAddress. In case this data was erased (3 or more password change operations have been performed since the operation on this server), the status will be 'noData'.

rlSshClientPasswordChangeFailureReason.name: rlSshClientPasswordChangeFailureReason
rlSshClientPasswordChangeFailureReason.description: In case the value of rlSshClientPasswordChangeStatus is 'failed', this field will contain the failure reason.

rlSshClientDeleteSelfKey.name: rlSshClientDeleteSelfKey
rlSshClientDeleteSelfKey.description: Setting to a value other than 'none' results in deleting the client self key of the chosen type.

rlSshClientRemoteServerPublicKeyFingerpr.name: rlSshClientRemoteServerPublicKeyFingerprintTable
rlSshClientRemoteServerPublicKeyFingerpr.description: Table for storing fingerprints of remote servers public keys. It is used for the purpose of server authentication. An entry can be inserted to this table either explicitly by user configuration, or during copy operation, after user's approval.

rlSshClientRemoteServerPublicKeyFingerpr.name: rlSshClientRemoteServerPublicKeyFingerprintEntry
rlSshClientRemoteServerPublicKeyFingerpr.description: The row definition for this table.

rlSshClientRemoteServersAuthenticationEn.name: rlSshClientRemoteServersAuthenticationEnable
rlSshClientRemoteServersAuthenticationEn.description: Setting this field to 'enable' enables remote servers authentication. As a result, while opening a session with a remote server, the fingerprint of the remote server will be computed and looked for in the table rlSshClientRemoteServerPublicKeyFingerprintTable. If an entry with the key (server-inet-address, server-fingerprint) is found, the server is considered authenticated. Otherwise, the server is not authenticated (unless the user specifically approved this server can be trusted).

rlSshClientDefaultKeyFlag.name: rlSshClientDefaultKeyFlag
